\caption{ \textbf{Two competing motors: the role of counter-torque}. The modified sketch of the two states of the motor, skewed by the external torque $M$ from the F${}_0$ motor. Now, in addition to the ATP-activated ratchet motor driving the shaft anticlockwise, there are two factors that promote the clockwise rotation: the biased diffusion in the tilted periodic potential $E_1(\theta,M)$ and the drift of the diffusion envelope with the constant rate  $MD/k_BT$. }
\label{fig8}
